**SEG-WE-1 (Sonnet 4.6):** Add new "Cohort" tab to MnemosyneC main window. File: `src/renderer/components/MnemosyneTabView.tsx` (or wherever tabs are registered — check the tab registration pattern used by the existing 14 tabs). Add tab entry: icon (use a network/mesh icon from existing icon set, or a simple speech bubble), label "Cohort", route/panel identifier "cohort". Create empty `CohortView.tsx` component shell at `src/renderer/components/CohortView.tsx` that renders a placeholder `<div>Cohort loading...</div>`. Wire the tab so clicking it renders CohortView. No logic yet — shell only. Verify in packaged build that the tab appears and clicking it does not crash.

**SEG-WE-2 (Sonnet 4.6):** Live message stream component. Create `src/renderer/components/CohortMessageStream.tsx`. Backing: poll `~/.mnemosynec/messages.jsonl` every 2 seconds via IPC (expose a `window.amplify.getMessages(client_id)` IPC handler if not already present — maps to the MCP `check_messages(client_id)` tool already wired in Wave D). Render each message as a chat bubble row: sender label (Founder / Bishop / Knight / Rook / Pawn — derived from the `from` field), ISO timestamp formatted as local time, body text. Chronological scroll, newest at bottom. Auto-scroll to bottom on new message (use a `useEffect` + ref pattern). Empty state: "No messages yet. Send one below." If IPC call fails (client_id not configured): show "Cohort not connected — apply MCP patches and restart." Wire this component into CohortView.tsx above the input area.

**SEG-WE-3 (Sonnet 4.6):** Founder input surface. Add to `CohortView.tsx` below the message stream: a `<textarea>` for message body (3-4 rows, resizable), a `<select>` dropdown for addressed_to with options: "Bishop" (value: "bishop"), "Knight" (value: "knight"), "Cohort broadcast" (value: "broadcast"). A "Send" button. Behavior on submit: call `window.amplify.sendMessage({ to: selectedTarget, from: 'founder', subject: auto_generate_subject(body), body })` — IPC handler maps to Wave D `send_message` MCP tool. The auto_generate_subject can be a truncated first 50 chars of body + "..." if longer. After successful send: clear the textarea, show a success toast "Message sent to [Bishop/Knight/Cohort]". After failure: show error toast "Send failed — check Cohort connection." Enter-to-send behavior: pressing Enter submits (Shift+Enter inserts newline). Every click produces visible feedback (`feedback_every_click_visible_feedback_canon_bp078`): Send button shows spinner during IPC call, reverts to "Send" on completion.

**SEG-WE-4 (Sonnet 4.6):** Socceri/pearl translation surface. Modify `CohortMessageStream.tsx` so each message bubble has a "Show raw" toggle link (small, below the body text). By default the toggle is collapsed and shows English body text only. When "Show raw" is clicked, expand a monospace `<pre>` panel below the message body showing: `canonical_ref`, `pearl_id`, `SID`, `slot_values` (as pretty-printed JSON), `decay_class`. These fields come from the raw JSONL record — expose them through the existing IPC layer (the `getMessages` handler should return the full JSONL record, not just the body). Hex/SID values in a distinct monospace style (use a `.cohort-raw` CSS class, `font-family: monospace`, `font-size: 0.8em`, `color: var(--text-secondary)`). Toggle text flips between "Show raw" and "Hide raw". This is the debug view — most Founders never open it. No change to default English rendering.

**SEG-WE-5 (Sonnet 4.6):** Channel filter tabs. Above the message stream in `CohortView.tsx`, add a row of filter tabs: "All", "Founder ↔ Bishop", "Founder ↔ Knight", "Bishop ↔ Knight", "Broadcast". Each filter tab is a button with active/inactive visual state. Default: "All" active. Filter logic applies on the local messages.jsonl read (client-side filter, no server round-trip): "Founder ↔ Bishop" = messages where (from='founder' AND to='bishop') OR (from='bishop' AND to='founder'); "Founder ↔ Knight" = same pattern with 'knight'; "Bishop ↔ Knight" = messages where (from='bishop' AND to='knight') OR (from='knight' AND to='bishop') — eavesdrop mode; "Broadcast" = messages where to='broadcast'. The `getMessages` IPC handler should return ALL messages (not pre-filtered), and the filter applies in the React component. Filter state: useState hook in CohortView. Re-renders stream on filter change.

**SEG-WE-6 (Sonnet 4.6):** Cohort round-trip verify (HARD BINDING per `feedback_ux_seg_screenshot_mandatory_bp078`). This SEG is the empirical proof that the full Wave E UI works end-to-end WITH BOTH MCP PATCHES APPLIED. Steps: (a) Confirm Gates 1-3 are GREEN (Gate 3 must have been verified before Wave E SEGs fired). (b) Open MnemosyneC packaged install (v0.1.42 or later), navigate to Cohort tab. (c) From the Founder input surface, type "Wave E verify: Bishop please acknowledge." addressed to Bishop. Click Send. (d) Capture screenshot of the Cohort tab showing the sent message in the stream. (e) Wait up to 30 seconds for Bishop to receive via check_messages and respond. (f) Capture screenshot of the Cohort tab showing Bishop's response in the stream with correct sender attribution + timestamp. (g) From the Founder input surface, send "Knight please acknowledge." addressed to Knight. (h) Capture screenshot of Knight's response appearing. (i) Send a "Cohort broadcast: Wave E online." to Cohort broadcast. (j) Capture screenshot showing broadcast message in All channel. All 4 screenshots required in Yoke-return. If any step fails: surface root cause with DevTools console output or IPC error log. Do NOT mark SEG-WE-6 complete with source-only verification.

**SEG-WE-7 (Sonnet 4.6) — LOCAL SCREENSHOT STORAGE PIPELINE:** Per `canon_mnemosynec_local_screenshot_storage_sid_addressed_no_token_burn_bp079_founder_ratify` (pearl_744d758cc19129c2). Add 3 MCP tools to MnemosyneC stdio shim + HTTP server: (a) `screenshot_capture()` — writes PNG to `~/.mnemosynec/screenshots/<yyyy-mm-dd>/<filename>.png` via Electron `desktopCapturer` or `robotjs`; computes SHA-256 SID; writes sidecar meta JSON; appends to `~/.mnemosynec/screenshots/index.jsonl`; emits pearl with `canonical_ref="screenshot:<sid>"` plus topic tags including source surface and timestamp; returns `{ sid, path, ts }`; (b) `screenshot_query(topic_tags[], from_ts?, to_ts?)` — reads index.jsonl, filters by topic_tags (any-match) and optional timestamp range, returns array of `{ sid, path, ts, tags, surface }`; (c) `screenshot_read(sid)` — looks up SID in index.jsonl, returns absolute local file path so AI cohort can use the `Read` tool directly; NO base64 in transit. Hotkey: `Ctrl+Shift+S` registered in Electron main process via `globalShortcut.register`; on trigger shows brief toast "Screenshot saved (SID: <first 8 chars>)". Index storage: `~/.mnemosynec/screenshots/index.jsonl` append-only. Cohort tab UI: add a "Screenshots" sub-section showing the 5 most recent screenshots as thumbnails via local `file://` img src, with SID + timestamp on hover.

